Game: **ChronoForge Arena**
Goal: Solo-dev viable. Mechanically superior. Controlled scope.

---

# 1️⃣ FULL MODULE TAXONOMY

We design modules by **System Layer**, not by flavor.

This prevents feature creep.

---

## 🧱 A. Structural Modules (Chassis Layer)

These define grid topology and physics behavior.

| Type             | Function                    | Risk           |
| ---------------- | --------------------------- | -------------- |
| Light Frame      | +Grid slots, low weight     | Low HP         |
| Reinforced Frame | +HP, heavier                | Torque stress  |
| Gyro Stabilizer  | Reduces imbalance penalty   | Power drain    |
| Shock Bracing    | Reduces recoil displacement | Adds weight    |
| Joint Lock       | Prevents limb detachment    | Increases heat |

Design rule:
Structural modules never deal damage.
They modify physics rules.

---

## ⚡ B. Power Modules

All combat modules require power routing.

| Type           | Effect                        | Risk                 |
| -------------- | ----------------------------- | -------------------- |
| Reactor Core   | Generates base power          | Heat spike           |
| Micro Reactor  | Cheap, unstable               | Overload chance      |
| Capacitor Bank | Stores burst power            | Explodes on overload |
| Power Router   | Improves adjacency efficiency | Fragile              |

Adjacency rule:
Each adjacent power module grants +X% efficiency.

---

## 🔥 C. Weapon Modules

Split by delivery model.

### Direct Fire

Railgun
Pulse Cannon
Plasma Saw

### Projectile

Missile Pod
Cluster Rocket
Shard Cannon

### Area

Shockwave Emitter
EMP Burst
Gravity Mine

Each weapon has:

* Power draw
* Recoil force
* Heat
* Firing delay
* Timeline cost

Weapons generate torque. That matters.

---

## 🛡 D. Defense Modules

Shields and mitigation must counter burst meta.

| Type             | Effect                               |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Kinetic Plating  | Flat damage reduction                |
| Reactive Armor   | Reduces next burst instance          |
| Energy Shield    | Rechargeable buffer                  |
| Reflective Field | Reflect % projectile damage          |
| Temporal Barrier | Reverts damage taken in last 1.2 sec |

Important:
Armor must scale against burst or meta collapses.

---

## 🌡 E. Thermal Modules

Prevents meltdown layer.

Heat Sink
Radiator Fan
Liquid Coolant Loop
Overdrive Vent (vent heat at HP cost)

Heat is quadrant-based, not global.

---

## ⏳ F. Temporal Modules (Signature Layer)

This is your mechanical edge.

### Tier 1 (Safe)

Rewind Shield
Future Sight (+accuracy)
Time Dilation (+initiative)

### Tier 2 (Risk)

Echo Cannon (duplicate projectile)
Pre-Fire Snapshot (attack 0.5s early)
Damage Revert (restore last 20% HP loss)

### Tier 3 (Danger)

Timeline Split (ghost clone for 1.5s)
Entropy Field (random stat boost each second)
Paradox Reactor (+50% power, +overload)

Each temporal module adds:
Paradox Load per second.

At 100%:
Random module permanently disabled.

This creates high skill ceiling builds.

---

## 🧠 G. AI / Behavior Modules

Add decision variance without real-time control.

Targeting Matrix (focus lowest HP)
Counter-Program (retaliate after hit)
Burst Logic (wait for max capacitor)

This increases build identity.

