# 3️⃣ MVP TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

Keep it deterministic.

---

## Engine

Godot 4 (GDScript)
Reason:
MIT licensed, no royalties
Fast iteration with built-in TileMap and scene tree
Deterministic simulation straightforward in GDScript
Exports to Desktop, Web, and Mobile

---

## Core Systems

### 1. Grid System

Data-driven 2D array.
Each cell stores:

* Module reference
* Heat value
* Structural load

---

### 2. Physics Lite Layer

Not real physics engine.

Compute:

* Center of mass
* Recoil impulse
* Torque imbalance

Apply:
Accuracy penalty
Movement drift
Stagger chance

No real-time rigid body simulation.

---

### 3. Simulation Engine

Combat is:
Tick-based deterministic loop.

Each tick:

* Resolve initiative
* Resolve power draw
* Apply recoil
* Apply damage
* Update heat
* Update paradox

This enables:
Async PvP snapshots.

---

### 4. Async PvP

Store:

* Build config JSON
* MMR rating

No real-time network.

Server optional at launch.
Can use:
Nakama (open source) / custom lightweight backend.

---

### 5. Replay Viewer

Record event log:

* Timestamps
* Damage
* Overload triggers
* Structural failure

Replay is visualized from log.

No video storage.

